<h2 class='date-header'><span>Thursday, November 27, 2014</span></h2>

          <div class="date-posts">
        
<div class='post-outer'>
<div class='post hentry uncustomized-post-template' itemprop='blogPost' itemscope='itemscope' itemtype='http://schema.org/BlogPosting'>
<meta content='https://scontent-1.2914.fna.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/10384527_854766457887044_6304784236648715734_n.jpg?oh=d2a46c8fade40ae2d6d15b6863d31d93&oe=551A9150' itemprop='image_url'/>
<meta content='36405856' itemprop='blogId'/>
<meta content='4118217509465570584' itemprop='postId'/>
<a name='4118217509465570584'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title' itemprop='name'>
<a href='https://askakorean.blogspot.com/2014/11/happy-thanksgiving.html'>Happy Thanksgiving!</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header'>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-body entry-content' id='post-body-4118217509465570584' itemprop='description articleBody'>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
Happy Thanksgiving to everyone! This year, TK is thankful for his first roasted turkey, a forward progress in his day job and his hobbies, renewed sense of faith, another year of wonderful marriage and another year of loyal readers for the AAK!</div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
<br /></div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
Meet Joseph Gobbles, TK's first attempt at roasted turkey. Joseph was delicious.</div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
<br /></div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
<img height="480" src="https://scontent-1.2914.fna.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/10384527_854766457887044_6304784236648715734_n.jpg?oh=d2a46c8fade40ae2d6d15b6863d31d93&amp;oe=551A9150" width="640" /></div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">
